            "favourites_count": 0,
            "edited_at": null,
            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://newsie.social/@TheConversationUS\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>TheConversationUS</span></a></span> <br>US biologist friend is often sent to problematic (climate change) areas by US government. They went to Texas that year, to discuss, among other things, salinisation &amp; what water use etc did to trees &amp; land. Never bothered them until they pointed out dying trees and patches of land that were, in effect, useless. These people cared a LOT about their trees &amp; land, so they got through because of it, and turned many local problems around.<br>Show people what affects them personally.</p>",
